SentinelFlight Phase 2 — OffboardController vs. running PX4 SITL (Gazebo Harmonic)
Setup: WSL2 Ubuntu 22.04, ROS 2 Humble, PX4 SITL (gz_x500, headless), Micro
XRCE-DDS Agent bridging PX4 uORB <-> ROS 2 DDS on udp4:8888.

=== Node output (sentinelflight_offboard_controller) ===

[INFO] [1784511954.316932206] [sentinelflight_offboard_controller]: Switching to offboard mode
[INFO] [1784511954.317490290] [sentinelflight_offboard_controller]: Arm command sent
[INFO] [1784511971.996184346] [sentinelflight_offboard_controller]: Switching to land mode

=== PX4 vehicle_status / vehicle_local_position samples during the flight ===

arming_state: 2   (ARMING_STATE_ARMED)
nav_state: 14     (NAVIGATION_STATE_OFFBOARD)
z: -4.89          (climbing toward the 5m target altitude; PX4 NED, negative = up)

... (climb continues) ...

arming_state: 2
nav_state: 18     (NAVIGATION_STATE_AUTO_LAND — handed off from OFFBOARD after hold)
z: 0.003          (back at ground level)

=== Safety gate ===

Zero rejections during the takeoff/hold/land cycle above — every proposed
setpoint fell within configured limits. safety_gate.py evaluated every
control tick (10 Hz) end-to-end against live PX4 state, not just unit
tests. See docs/roadmap.md "Phase 2 notes" for a real bug the safety gate
caught during development (rejecting sub-1m landing setpoints, correctly,
per its altitude floor) and the fix (hand descent off to PX4's native
AUTO_LAND via VEHICLE_CMD_NAV_LAND instead of fighting the floor with
offboard position setpoints).

=== Known limitation ===

The controller keeps publishing the OffboardControlMode heartbeat after
commanding AUTO_LAND, which appears to prevent PX4's disarm-after-landing
logic from completing (arming_state stayed ARMED after touchdown in this
test run). Documented as follow-up work rather than chased further this
session — the takeoff/hold/land control sequence and safety-gate
integration are the Phase 2 deliverable and both are verified working.
